PHP Language â€“ Introduction
PHP (Hypertext Preprocessor) is a popular server-side scripting language mainly used for web development. It runs on the server and generates dynamic web pages.
Key points:
Open-source and easy to learn
Works well with HTML, CSS, JavaScript
Supports databases like MySQL, PostgreSQL
Used for forms, sessions, authentication, APIs
Powers websites like blogs, e-commerce, CMS (e.g., WordPress)
